<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10051e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10051e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10051e"> 51(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> farmed out</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Si l&apos;histoire reste muette sur l&apos;origine des facteurs fran&ccedil;ais, il est &agrave; supposer que, sous le r&egrave;gne de Louis XIV, il devait y avoir des facteurs &agrave; Paris, au moment o&ugrave; la <mark>Ferme des Postes</mark> fut institu&eacute;e en 1672 et o&ugrave; Lazare Patin en devint propri&eacute;taire, moyennant une redevance annuelle d&apos;un million de livres. <font color="green">[If history says nothing about the origin of French postmen, one must suppose that under the reign of Louis XIV there must have been postmen in Paris at the time when the Farm of the Posts was instituted in 1672, and Lazare Patin became its owner for a yearly tax of a million pounds.]</font> <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) ?103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
